<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
          xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuBlockDocumentation">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Block_Documentation</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: Set or displays the user documentation for the selected block</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This menu allows to set or get user documentation for a block.
    </para>
    <para>
	The user documentation can be edited and displayed by a user
	defined function. The supplied <literal>standard_doc</literal>
	function is proposed as default.
    </para>
    <para>
      If a user documentation has been given for the selected block
      based on <literal>standard_doc</literal>, this menu displays it
      in as small edition widget. If no documentation exists a first
      dialog proposes to use the <literal>standard_doc</literal>
      function or to select another user-defined function. With the
      <literal>standard_doc</literal> choice a small edition widget
      opens allowing to enter the documentation.
    </para>
    <para> 
      The documentation data are saved as a text array in the
      <literal>doc</literal> field of the block (see <link
      linkend="scicos_block">scicos block data structure</link>).
    </para>

  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member> <link linkend="scicos_block">scicos block data structure</link> </member>
      <member> <link linkend="XcosSelect">Select</link> </member>
     </simplelist>
   </refsection>
</refentry>
